E. Share insights for Q2.d. [1 Marks]

*The vehicle with 3 and 5 cylinders are less in number in the dataset provided.

*Light weight range is from 1500 to 2500,mid weight range is from 2500 to 3500 and heavy weight range is from 3500 to >5000

*Also the displacement is between 50 to 100 for 3 cylinder vehicles and between 100 to 200 in 5 cylinder vehicle and these vehicles have weights ranging from low range to mid range

*The vehicles with 4 cylinders are having a displacement ranging from 50 to 150 and are more prevalent with less weights ranging from 1500 to 3250

*The vehicles with 6 cylinders are having a displacement ranging from 150 to 250 and their weights range from 2500 to 4000.

*The last category are heavy weight vehicles with 8 cylinders and their displacement is highest ranging between 250 to 450

*From plot we infer that vehicles with 6 cylinders still have many vehicles with less weight or weights in midrange with better displacement than vehicles with 3 to 5 cylinders

In [27]:
from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
clusters=range(2,10)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(Cars)
    prediction=model.predict(Cars)
    meanDistortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(Cars, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / Cars.shape[0])

B. Plot a visual and find elbow point. [2 Marks]

In [28]:
plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method')
plt.show()

C. On the above visual, highlight which are the possible Elbow points. [1 Marks]

The elbow takes a steep descend at cluster size 3 and 4 and beyond these the graph is a gradual descend curve
The optimal number of clusters from elbow is 4

5. Data Understanding & Cleaning: [5 Marks]¶

A. Explain pre-requisite/assumptions of PCA. [2 Marks]

PCA does not require statistical assumptions. However, it is sensitive to the scale of the data. As a result, the data must be standardized (standard deviation = 1 and mean =0). This means that column means in the np matrix will be 0. The PCA of the data needs to be based on the correlation matrix, not on the covariance matrix. Note that the principal components predict the observed covariance matrix.*
